# Component Conventions

## Server vs client

- Default to **server components**. Add `"use client"` only when you need browser APIs (scroll, refs, `useState`, event handlers on interactive elements like the side-nav).
- Currently client-only: `Header`, `SideNav`, `Newsletter` (form handler).

## File layout

- Components: `app/_components/<Name>.tsx`
- Section components: `app/_components/sections/<Name>.tsx`
- Hooks: `app/_lib/<useThing>.ts`
- One default-exported component per file; PascalCase filename matches export.

## Conventions

- Use `next/image` for any image (never `<img>`); `next/link` for internal nav.
- Use Tailwind utility classes — no CSS modules unless tokens cannot express it.
- Reach for design tokens (`bg-bg`, `text-accent`, etc.) instead of raw hex values.
- Prefer `clsx`-style template literals only when conditionally toggling classes; otherwise plain strings.
- Do **not** add narrating comments (e.g. `// render hero`). Comments only for non-obvious intent.
- Keep section components self-contained — pass no props from `page.tsx`; they own their own copy and image URL.

## Accessibility

- Header nav buttons that open the side drawer must use `aria-controls`, `aria-expanded`, and visible focus rings.
- Decorative images: `alt=""`. Content images: meaningful `alt`.
- The mobile hamburger needs an `aria-label` and a screen-reader-only label.
